<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-15T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="230" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/335a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                                (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-15T17:00:00-04:00">July 15,
                                    1935—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>154. For <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">Bullitt</persName> from Secretary
                                <persName corresp="#p_MHJ1">Morgenthau</persName>. Congratulations
                            on breaking the log jam between the United States and Russia.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PW1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>[For text of the agreement effected by exchange of notes July 13,
                                1935, see Department of State Executive Agreement Series No. 81, or
                                49 Stat. 3805. For text of press release issued by the Department of
                                State, July 13, 1935, see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, July 13, 1935, page 45.]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>